ciscoWirelessP2pBpiMIB.name: ciscoWirelessP2pBpiMIB
ciscoWirelessP2pBpiMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-wireless@cisco.com
ciscoWirelessP2pBpiMIB.description: This is the MIB Module for the Baseline Privacy Interface (BPI) at Point to Point Wireless Radio Card. This is a specialization on the MCNS docsBpiMib for Cisco Wireless point to point communication links.

cwrBpiRsBaseTable.name: cwrBpiRsBaseTable
cwrBpiRsBaseTable.description: Describes the basic and authorization-related Baseline Privacy attributes of each Slave Radio interface.

cwrBpiRsBaseEntry.name: cwrBpiRsBaseEntry
cwrBpiRsBaseEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of one Slave Radio interface. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of ciscoWirelessP2P.

cwrBpiRsPrivacyEnable.name: cwrBpiRsPrivacyEnable
cwrBpiRsPrivacyEnable.description: This object identifies whether the Slave Radio is provisioned to use Encryption or not.

cwrBpiRsPublicKey.name: cwrBpiRsPublicKey
cwrBpiRsPublicKey.description: Public key of the Radio Slave encoded as an ASN.1 SubjectPublicKeyInfo object as defined in the RSA Encryption Standard (PKCS #1) [RSA1].

cwrBpiRsAuthState.name: cwrBpiRsAuthState
cwrBpiRsAuthState.description: The state of the Radio Slave authorization FSM. The start state indicates that FSM is in its initial state.

cwrBpiRsAuthKeySequenceNumber.name: cwrBpiRsAuthKeySequenceNumber
cwrBpiRsAuthKeySequenceNumber.description: The authorization key sequence number for this FSM.

cwrBpiRsAuthExpires.name: cwrBpiRsAuthExpires
cwrBpiRsAuthExpires.description: The number of seconds left before the current authorization for this FSM expires. If the Radio Slave does not have an active authorization, then this value is 0.

cwrBpiRsAuthReset.name: cwrBpiRsAuthReset
cwrBpiRsAuthReset.description: Setting this object to TRUE generates a Reauthorize event in the authorization FSM, as described in section 4.1.2.3.4 of the Baseline Privacy Interface Specification. Reading this object always returns FALSE.

cwrBpiRsAuthGraceTime.name: cwrBpiRsAuthGraceTime
cwrBpiRsAuthGraceTime.description: Grace time for an authorization key. A Radio Slave is expected to start trying to get a new authorization key beginning AuthGraceTime seconds before the authorization key actually expires. The value of this object cannot be changed while the authorization state machine is running. NOTE: When installed in the field, this variable should NEVER be set below 300 which is the lower limit by standard. This variable accepts a wider range to facilitate testing.

cwrBpiRsTEKGraceTime.name: cwrBpiRsTEKGraceTime
cwrBpiRsTEKGraceTime.description: Grace time for a TEK. A Radio Slave is expected to start trying to get a new TEK beginning TEKGraceTime seconds before the TEK actually expires. The value of this object cannot be changed while the authorization state machine is running. NOTE: When installed in the field, this variable should NEVER be set below 300 which is the lower limit by standard. This variable accepts a wider range to facilitate testing.

cwrBpiRsAuthWaitTimeout.name: cwrBpiRsAuthWaitTimeout
cwrBpiRsAuthWaitTimeout.description: Authorize Wait Timeout. The value of this object cannot be changed while the authorization state machine is running.

cwrBpiRsReauthWaitTimeout.name: cwrBpiRsReauthWaitTimeout
cwrBpiRsReauthWaitTimeout.description: Reauthorize Wait Timeout in seconds. The value of this object cannot be changed while the authorization state machine is running.

cwrBpiRsOpWaitTimeout.name: cwrBpiRsOpWaitTimeout
cwrBpiRsOpWaitTimeout.description: Operational Wait Timeout in seconds. The value of this object cannot be changed while the authorization state machine is running.

cwrBpiRsRekeyWaitTimeout.name: cwrBpiRsRekeyWaitTimeout
cwrBpiRsRekeyWaitTimeout.description: Rekey Wait Timeout in seconds. The value of this object cannot be changed while the authorization state machine is running.

cwrBpiRsAuthRequests.name: cwrBpiRsAuthRequests
cwrBpiRsAuthRequests.description: Count of times the Radio Slave has transmitted an Authorization Request message.

cwrBpiRsAuthReplies.name: cwrBpiRsAuthReplies
cwrBpiRsAuthReplies.description: Count of times the Radio Slave has received an Authorization Reply message.

cwrBpiRsAuthInvalids.name: cwrBpiRsAuthInvalids
cwrBpiRsAuthInvalids.description: Count of times the Radio Slave has received an Authorization Invalid message.

cwrBpiRsAuthInvalidErrorCode.name: cwrBpiRsAuthInvalidErrorCode
cwrBpiRsAuthInvalidErrorCode.description: Error-Code in most recent Authorization Invalid message received by the Radio Slave. On bootup, this has value no-information(0). At all other times, this object reflects the error code received

cwrBpiRsAuthInvalidErrorString.name: cwrBpiRsAuthInvalidErrorString
cwrBpiRsAuthInvalidErrorString.description: Display-String in most recent Authorization Invalid message received by the Radio Slave. This is a zero length string if no Authorization Invalid message has been received since reboot.

cwrBpiRsTEKTable.name: cwrBpiRsTEKTable
cwrBpiRsTEKTable.description: Describes the attributes of each Radio Slave Traffic Encryption Key (TEK) Service.

cwrBpiRsTEKEntry.name: cwrBpiRsTEKEntry
cwrBpiRsTEKEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing the TEK attributes of one instantiated TEK service. There will be one such entry for every Radio Slave of a P2P link.

cwrBpiRsTEKEncryptionNegotiated.name: cwrBpiRsTEKEncryptionNegotiated
cwrBpiRsTEKEncryptionNegotiated.description: This identifies whether this TEK service is using encryption or not. Encryption may not be in use even though cwrBpiRsPrivacyEnable is provisioned. This is possible if the remote is not configured for privacy or it's not running an encryption capable image.

cwrBpiRsTEKState.name: cwrBpiRsTEKState
cwrBpiRsTEKState.description: The state of the indicated TEK FSM. The start(1) state indicates that FSM is in its initial state.

cwrBpiRsTEKExpiresOld.name: cwrBpiRsTEKExpiresOld
cwrBpiRsTEKExpiresOld.description: The number of seconds left to expire for the oldest active key for this FSM. If this FSM has no active keys then this value will be zero.

cwrBpiRsTEKExpiresNew.name: cwrBpiRsTEKExpiresNew
cwrBpiRsTEKExpiresNew.description: The number of seconds left to expire for the newest active key for this FSM. If this FSM has no active keys then this value will be zero.

cwrBpiRsTEKKeyRequests.name: cwrBpiRsTEKKeyRequests
cwrBpiRsTEKKeyRequests.description: Count of times the this TEK Service has transmitted a Key Request message.

cwrBpiRsTEKKeyReplies.name: cwrBpiRsTEKKeyReplies
cwrBpiRsTEKKeyReplies.description: Count of times this TEK Service has received a Key Reply message.

cwrBpiRsTEKInvalids.name: cwrBpiRsTEKInvalids
cwrBpiRsTEKInvalids.description: Count of times this TEK Service has received a TEK Invalid message.

cwrBpiRsTEKAuthPends.name: cwrBpiRsTEKAuthPends
cwrBpiRsTEKAuthPends.description: Count of times an Authorization Pending (Auth Pend) event occurred in this TEK Serivce FSM.

cwrBpiRsTEKInvalidErrorCode.name: cwrBpiRsTEKInvalidErrorCode
cwrBpiRsTEKInvalidErrorCode.description: Error-Code in most recent TEK Invalid message received by this TEK service. On bootup, this has value no-information(0). At all other times, this object reflects the error code received

cwrBpiRsTEKInvalidErrorString.name: cwrBpiRsTEKInvalidErrorString
cwrBpiRsTEKInvalidErrorString.description: Display-String in most recent TEK Invalid message received by this TEK Service. This is a zero length string if no TEK Invalid message has been received since this TEK Service was started.

cwrBpiRmAuthTable.name: cwrBpiRmAuthTable
cwrBpiRmAuthTable.description: Describes the attributes of each Radio Master authorization association. The Radio master maintains one authorization association with each Baseline Privacy-enabled Radio Slave on each Radio Master MAC interface.

cwrBpiRmAuthEntry.name: cwrBpiRmAuthEntry
cwrBpiRmAuthEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of one authorization association. The Radio master MUST create one entry per Radio Slave per MAC interface, based on the receipt of an Authorization Request message, and MUST not delete the entry before the Radio Slave authorization permanently expires.

cwrBpiRmAuthPrivacyEnable.name: cwrBpiRmAuthPrivacyEnable
cwrBpiRmAuthPrivacyEnable.description: This object identifies whether the Master Radio is provisioned to use Encryption or not.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsPublicKey.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsPublicKey
cwrBpiRmAuthRsPublicKey.description: Public key of the Radio Slave encoded as an ASN.1 SubjectPublicKeyInfo object as defined in the RSA Encryption Standard (PKCS #1) [RSA1]. This is a zero-length string if the Radio Master does not retain the public key.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsKeySequenceNumber.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsKeySequenceNumber
cwrBpiRmAuthRsKeySequenceNumber.description: The authorization key sequence number for this Radio Slave.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsExpires.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsExpires
cwrBpiRmAuthRsExpires.description: The number of seconds left before the current authorization for this Radio Slave expires. If this Radio Slave does not have an active authorization, then the value is zero.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsLifetime.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsLifetime
cwrBpiRmAuthRsLifetime.description: Lifetime, in seconds, the Radio Master assigns to an authorization key for this Radio Slave. NOTE: When installed in the field, this variable should NEVER be set below 86400 which is the lower limit by standard. This variable accepts a wider range to facilitate testing.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsReset.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsReset
cwrBpiRmAuthRsReset.description: Setting this object to True(1) causes the Radio Master to invalidate the current Radio Slave authorization key, to transmit an Authorization Invalid message to the Radio Slave, and to invalidate the unicast TEK associated with this Radio Slave authorization. Reading this object always returns False

cwrBpiRmAuthRsRequests.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsRequests
cwrBpiRmAuthRsRequests.description: Count of times the Radio Master has received an Authorization Request message from this Radio Slave.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsReplies.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsReplies
cwrBpiRmAuthRsReplies.description: Count of times the Radio master has transmitted an Authorization Reply message to this Radio Slave.

cwrBpiRmAuthRsInvalids.name: cwrBpiRmAuthRsInvalids
cwrBpiRmAuthRsInvalids.description: Count of times the Radio Master has transmitted an Authorization Invalid message to this Radio Slave.

cwrBpiRmAuthInvalidErrorCode.name: cwrBpiRmAuthInvalidErrorCode
cwrBpiRmAuthInvalidErrorCode.description: Error-Code in most recent Authorization Invalid message transmitted to the Radio Slave. On bootup, this has value no-information(0). At all other times, this object reflects the error code transmitted

cwrBpiRmAuthInvalidErrorString.name: cwrBpiRmAuthInvalidErrorString
cwrBpiRmAuthInvalidErrorString.description: Display-String in most recent Authorization Invalid message transmitted to the Radio Slave. This is a zero length string if no Authorization Invalid message has been transmitted to the Radio Slave.

cwrBpiRmTEKTable.name: cwrBpiRmTEKTable
cwrBpiRmTEKTable.description: Describes the attributes of each Radio Slave Traffic Encryption Key (TEK) association. The Radio master maintains one TEK association for the Radio Slave.

cwrBpiRmTEKEntry.name: cwrBpiRmTEKEntry
cwrBpiRmTEKEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of one TEK service on a particular Radio Master MAC interface. The Radio Master MUST create one entry per TEK Service per MAC interface, based on the receipt of an Key Request message, and MUST not delete the entry before the Radio Slave authorization for that TEK Service permanently expires.

cwrBpiRmTEKEncryptionNegotiated.name: cwrBpiRmTEKEncryptionNegotiated
cwrBpiRmTEKEncryptionNegotiated.description: This identifies whether this TEK service is using encryption or not. Encryption may not be in use even though cwrBpiRmAuthPrivacyEnable is provisioned. This is possible if the master is not configured for privacy or it's not running an encryption capable image.

cwrBpiRmTEKLifetime.name: cwrBpiRmTEKLifetime
cwrBpiRmTEKLifetime.description: Lifetime, in seconds, the Radio Master assigns to keys for this TEK association. NOTE: When installed in the field, this variable should NEVER be set below 1800 which is the lower limit by standard. This variable accepts a wider range to facilitate testing.

cwrBpiRmTEKExpiresOld.name: cwrBpiRmTEKExpiresOld
cwrBpiRmTEKExpiresOld.description: The number of seconds left to expire for the oldest active key for this TEK association. If this TEK associateion has no active key then the value will be zero.

cwrBpiRmTEKExpiresNew.name: cwrBpiRmTEKExpiresNew
cwrBpiRmTEKExpiresNew.description: The number of seconds left to expire for the newest active key for this TEK association. If this TEK association has no active keys then this value will be zero.

cwrBpiRmTEKReset.name: cwrBpiRmTEKReset
cwrBpiRmTEKReset.description: Setting this object to TRUE causes the Radio Master to invalidate the current active TEK(s) (plural due to key transition periods), and to generate a new TEK. Reading this object always returns FALSE.

cwrBpiRmKeyRequests.name: cwrBpiRmKeyRequests
cwrBpiRmKeyRequests.description: Count of times the Radio Master has received a Key Request message.

cwrBpiRmKeyReplies.name: cwrBpiRmKeyReplies
cwrBpiRmKeyReplies.description: Count of times the Radio master has transmitted a Key Reply message.

cwrBpiRmTEKInvalids.name: cwrBpiRmTEKInvalids
cwrBpiRmTEKInvalids.description: Count of times the Radio Master has transmitted a TEK Invalid message.

cwrBpiRmTEKInvalidErrorCode.name: cwrBpiRmTEKInvalidErrorCode
cwrBpiRmTEKInvalidErrorCode.description: Error-Code in most recent TEK Invalid message sent in association with this TEK service. On bootup, this has value no-information(0). At all other times, this object reflects the error code received

cwrBpiRmTEKInvalidErrorString.name: cwrBpiRmTEKInvalidErrorString
cwrBpiRmTEKInvalidErrorString.description: Display-String in the most recent TEK Invalid message sent in ssociation with this BPI TEK service. This is a zero length string if no TEK Invalid message has been received since reboot.

cwrBpiBasicCompliance.name: cwrBpiBasicCompliance
cwrBpiBasicCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices which implement the Cisco Wireless Radio point to point Baseline Privacy Interface.

cwrBpiRsGroup.name: cwrBpiRsGroup
cwrBpiRsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Radio Slave BPI status and control.

cwrBpiRmGroup.name: cwrBpiRmGroup
cwrBpiRmGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Radio Master BPI status and control.
